# 4ALL – Space of Connection

4ALL is an open space.  
It connects layers without naming them.  
4ALL shows what can be visible at the same time.

ASCII Forms:

●────●  
1D: Connection.

●────●  
│    │  
●────●  
2D: Surface, open area.

     ●────●  
    /    /│  
  ●────● │  
  │    │ ●  
  │    │/  
  ●────●  
3D: Body, multi‑view.

4ALL provides:
- open spaces  
- multi‑connections  
- neutral grouping  
- visible structure without internals  

4ALL today:  
A space that can hold anything without demanding anything.  
Neutral. Clear. Visible.
